The paper focuses on software startups and their evolution through business hypothesis testing, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of ethnography and post-mortem analysis suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybernetics (cs.CY). The visualization of entrepreneurial knowledge flow suggests a focus on social and information sciences (cs.SI) and complex systems (cs.CC).
